<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 11:54AM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Washington County through 1230 PM MDT...
At 1154 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Apple Valley, or near Colorado City, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Zion National Park, Apple Valley, Springdale and Rockville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
